The most common bug to avoid in the 0/1 knapsack problem is not properly handling the base case or the recursive/iterative approach, leading to incorrect or inefficient solutions, such as exceeding the capacity or not considering all possible combinations of items.

```python
def knapsack_01(weights, values, capacity):
    n = len(values)
    dp = [[0 for _ in range(capacity + 1)] for _ in range(n + 1)]
    for i in range(n + 1):
        for w in range(capacity + 1):
            if i == 0 or w == 0:
                dp[i][w] = 0
            elif weights[i-1] <= w:
                dp[i][w] = max(values[i-1] + dp[i-1][w-weights[i-1]], dp[i-1][w])
            else:
                dp[i][w] = dp[i-1][w]
